# Git commit workflow

After finishing a **logical batch** of edits (one feature, one fix, one coherent refactor, or one documentation/rules update), **create a git commit** with a clear message before moving on to unrelated work.

- Do not leave large uncommitted mixed changes when switching tasks.
- If a batch is incomplete, it is fine to wait until that batch is done before committing.
